<head>COURT DRESS</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">官服</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>GARMENT APPROPRIATE to be WORN at COURT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general ancient term for formal dress, for what one is wearing when properly dressed up is fú 服.</p>
<p>2. Páo 袍 became the current word for formal court dress, indicating rank, in Han times.</p>
<p>3. Fú fǔ 黻黼 refers to the richly embroidered court dress reserved for highly formal special occasions.</p>
<p>4. Shān 衫 informal wide-sleeved jacket of an official, sometimes with indications of his rank.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
